WEBVTT

00:02.002 --> 00:03.704
[siren blaring]

00:03.737 --> 00:04.572
- I NEED YOU TO MOVE, JOHN.
WE'RE LOSING HIM.

00:04.605 --> 00:05.539
- SH--. TWO MINUTES AWAY.

00:05.573 --> 00:07.208
- ALMOST NO PULSE.

00:07.241 --> 00:08.709
- COME ON, SIR.
COME ON, COME ON, COME ON.

00:08.742 --> 00:10.344
HEY, I THINK HE'S TRYING
TO SAY SOMETHING.

00:10.378 --> 00:11.312
HE'S TRYING TO SAY SOMETHING.
- HE'S IN V-FIB.

00:11.345 --> 00:13.547
WE GOTTA SHOCK HIM.

00:13.581 --> 00:14.982
- I-I LOVE--
- HE'S TRYING TO SAY SOMETHING.

00:15.015 --> 00:16.384
WHAT IS IT, SIR?
COME ON, SIR.

00:16.417 --> 00:17.351
- GET READY TO CLEAR, BRI.
- WHAT IS IT?

00:17.385 --> 00:19.487
- TA CAFFERIN...

00:19.520 --> 00:21.489
- BRI?

00:21.522 --> 00:24.092
- [mumbling]
I LOVE HER.

00:24.125 --> 00:25.259
- CLEAR.

00:25.293 --> 00:29.363
[flatlining]

00:29.397 --> 00:31.265
CLEAR.

00:31.299 --> 00:32.433
[flatlining]

00:32.466 --> 00:34.202
CLEAR.

00:34.235 --> 00:37.371
- SH--.

00:37.405 --> 00:38.906
HE CLEARLY SAID,
"TELL CATHERINE I LOVE HER."

00:38.939 --> 00:40.241
- I HEARD,
"CATHETER'S BROKEN."

00:40.274 --> 00:41.842
- CATHETER?
YOU WERE TOO FAR AWAY.

00:41.875 --> 00:43.077
- I WAS RIGHT NEXT TO YOU.
- WHAT'D YOU HEAR?

00:43.111 --> 00:44.112
- "THE CATHOLIC POKER."

00:44.145 --> 00:45.579
- WHAT THE HECK
WOULD THAT MEAN?

00:45.613 --> 00:47.047
- MAYBE SOME PRIEST
HAD A HARD-ON FOR HIM.

00:47.081 --> 00:48.782
PEOPLE SAY STRANGE SH--
WHEN THEY KICK, BRIAN.

00:48.816 --> 00:50.451
WE HAD A GIANT BROTHER
GO ON US FOUR MONTHS AGO.

00:50.484 --> 00:52.420
SAME DEAL,
HEART ATTACK, 52,

00:52.453 --> 00:53.921
BUILT LIKE A BRICK SH--HOUSE,

00:53.954 --> 00:56.724
EX-HEAVYWEIGHT BOXER,
NECK THE SIZE OF AN SUV.

00:56.757 --> 00:57.525
- HE CALLS ME CLOSE,
I LEAN IN.

00:57.558 --> 00:59.127
YOU KNOW WHAT HE SAYS?

00:59.160 --> 01:00.361
"HANNAH MONTANA."

01:00.394 --> 01:01.695
- HAD AN OLD LADY
LAST SUMMER.

01:01.729 --> 01:03.864
96-YEAR-OLD
GREAT GRANDMOTHER,

01:03.897 --> 01:06.267
WHITE, JEWISH,
SURVIVED AUSCHWITZ.

01:06.300 --> 01:07.268
YOU KNOW WHAT
HER LAST WORDS WERE?

01:07.301 --> 01:08.802
"SALSA."

01:08.836 --> 01:10.738
- I HOPE MY DYING WORDS
ARE HAPPY.

01:10.771 --> 01:12.373
- I HOPE MY DYING WORDS ARE
"THAT WAS THE BEST

01:12.406 --> 01:13.607
"BLOW JOB EVER.

01:13.641 --> 01:15.042
THANK YOU,
NEIL PATRICK HARRIS."

01:15.075 --> 01:16.610
- HE WAS WEARING
A WEDDING RING.

01:16.644 --> 01:18.279
I OWE IT TO HIS WIFE
TO TELL HER THAT

01:18.312 --> 01:20.080
HIS DYING BREATH,
THE LAST WORDS

01:20.114 --> 01:21.415
HE EVER SPOKE
ON PLANET EARTH,

01:21.449 --> 01:23.817
INVOLVED HIS ETERNAL LOVE
FOR HER.

01:23.851 --> 01:25.386
- BRIAN, WE HAVEN'T
EVEN ESTABLISHED

01:25.419 --> 01:27.155
THAT HE SAID THE WORD
"CATHERINE."

01:27.188 --> 01:28.556
AND EVEN IF HE DID,
HE COULD BE TALKING ABOUT

01:28.589 --> 01:30.391
HIS CAMARO OR HIS DICK.

01:30.424 --> 01:31.892
- WHO NAMES
THEIR DICK CATHERINE?

01:31.925 --> 01:33.494
- A GUY WHO DRIVES A CAMARO.
- OKAY.

01:33.527 --> 01:35.296
- I'M SORRY, MRS. HARRIS,

01:35.329 --> 01:37.465
BUT WE DID
ALL THAT WE COULD DO.

01:37.498 --> 01:39.733
- OH.
[crying]

01:39.767 --> 01:41.335
- HARRIS?
THAT'S HER.

01:41.369 --> 01:42.736
THAT'S CATHERINE,
THE GUY'S WIFE.

01:42.770 --> 01:44.138
- BRIAN, DO NOT
GET INVOLVED.

01:44.172 --> 01:45.306
- BRIAN, SOMETIMES
WE SAVE LIVES.

01:45.339 --> 01:46.607
SOMETIMES WE CAN'T.

01:46.640 --> 01:48.108
BUT WE DO NOT
CROSS THE LINE

01:48.142 --> 01:49.677
WHEN IT COMES TO A FAMILY
IN THEIR GRIEF.

01:49.710 --> 01:53.113
- HE LOVED HER.
I OWE IT TO HIM.

01:53.147 --> 01:55.949
IT IS MY MORAL OBLIGATION.

02:00.321 --> 02:04.692
I-I WORKED ON
TRYING TO SAVE MR. HARRIS.

02:04.725 --> 02:08.329
AND HE HAD SOME IMPORTANT

02:08.362 --> 02:10.364
PARTING WORDS
FOR HIS WIFE.

02:10.398 --> 02:12.099
- OH, MY GOD.
- YES.

02:12.132 --> 02:15.436
IT WAS VERY TOUCHING.

02:15.469 --> 02:17.738
HE SAID, "TELL C--

02:19.240 --> 02:24.912
AGNES I SAID HI."

02:27.248 --> 02:29.149
- CAHAGNES?

02:29.183 --> 02:31.552
- HE HAD SOME
TRACHEAL BLOCKAGE.

02:31.585 --> 02:32.986
- IT'S, LIKE, A THROAT THING.

02:33.020 --> 02:34.355
[coughs] CAHAGNES.
IT'S VERY COMMON.

02:34.388 --> 02:35.623
- OH.

02:35.656 --> 02:38.292
WELL, WHY WOULD HE
JUST SAY HI?

02:38.326 --> 02:40.027
- MA'AM, DID YOUR--
DID YOUR HUSBAND--

02:40.060 --> 02:42.830
DID HE DRIVE A CAMARO?

02:42.863 --> 02:44.498
- I'M SORRY,
MA'AM, HE'S NEW.

02:44.532 --> 02:45.799
WHAT YOUR HUSBAND SAID WAS,

02:45.833 --> 02:47.067
"TELL AGNES
THAT I LOVE HER."

02:47.100 --> 02:48.402
- "SHE MADE LIFE
WORTH LIVING."

02:48.436 --> 02:50.170
- AND THEN HE SMILED.
- PASSED ON.

02:50.204 --> 02:52.306
- OH, MY GOD.

02:52.340 --> 02:54.174
THAT'S BEAUTIFUL.

02:54.208 --> 02:56.577
- YES, IT WAS.

02:56.610 --> 02:59.413
- WE'RE SORRY FOR YOUR LOSS.

03:01.582 --> 03:04.518
- WE GOT TO GO.

03:04.552 --> 03:07.221
[funky music]

03:07.255 --> 03:10.491
*

03:10.524 --> 03:11.992
- I DON'T TELL LIES.

03:12.025 --> 03:13.594
I LIVE MY LIFE ACCORDING
TO A MORAL COMPASS.

03:13.627 --> 03:15.062
DON'T YOU GUYS?

03:15.095 --> 03:16.230
- NO, I DON'T HAVE
A MORAL COMPASS.

03:16.264 --> 03:17.698
I GOT A MORAL GPS, OKAY?

03:17.731 --> 03:19.099
IT OFFERS UP THREE ROUTES

03:19.132 --> 03:20.568
IN ALMOST
ANY GIVEN SITUATION:

03:20.601 --> 03:22.336
A WHITE LIE,
AN OFF-WHITE LIE,

03:22.370 --> 03:25.172
AND THE LONG, LONELY ROUTE
OF TRUTH AND HONESTY

03:25.205 --> 03:26.607
THAT SKIPS ALL TOLL ROADS

03:26.640 --> 03:28.208
AND USUALLY ENDS
IN COMPLETE DISASTER,

03:28.242 --> 03:30.043
WHICH IS WHY
I RARELY TAKE IT.

03:30.077 --> 03:31.379
- MY PENIS IS MY COMPASS.
- AND IT ONLY POINTS

03:31.412 --> 03:33.046
IN ONE DIRECTION: THERESA.

03:33.080 --> 03:35.048
- YOU JUST MADE MY COMPASS
SEEM A LOT LESS COOL.

03:35.082 --> 03:36.884
- I THINK WE SHOULD LOCATE
THIS CATHERINE LADY.

03:36.917 --> 03:38.519
- MY DICK SAYS
WE SHOULD LOCATE LUNCH.

03:38.552 --> 03:40.354
- SHE WAS THE LOVE
OF HIS LIFE, JOHNNY.

03:40.388 --> 03:42.390
- NO, HIS WIFE WAS.
WE JUST TOLD HER SO.

03:42.423 --> 03:43.591
- WHAT ARE YOU GONNA DO,
LOOK UP

03:43.624 --> 03:45.092
EVERY CATHERINE IN CHICAGO?
BESIDES,

03:45.125 --> 03:46.427
IS CATHERINE WITH A "C"?
KATHERINE WITH A "K"?

03:46.460 --> 03:47.795
- AND YOU KNOW THERE'S
A BLACK GIRL

03:47.828 --> 03:48.729
OUT THERE SPELLING IT
WITH A "Q".

03:48.762 --> 03:49.563
- OH, WE DO LOVE OUR Qs,

03:49.597 --> 03:50.698
EXCEPT FOR KWANZAA.

03:50.731 --> 03:52.132
I DON'T KNOW HOW THE HELL

03:52.165 --> 03:53.401
WE DROPPED THE BALL
ON THAT ONE.

03:53.434 --> 03:56.136
- WHOA, WHOA, WHOA.
[shushes]

03:56.169 --> 03:57.405
I GUESS WE'RE GETTING MEXICAN.

03:57.438 --> 04:00.708
- [laughs]

04:00.741 --> 04:01.909
KNOW WHAT'S
EVEN MORE DISTURBING

04:01.942 --> 04:03.644
THAN BRIAN'S MORAL COMPASS?

04:03.677 --> 04:04.812
- THAT JOHNNY'S PENIS
KNOWS WHERE TO GET

04:04.845 --> 04:06.714
THE BEST CARNITAS IN TOWN?

04:06.747 --> 04:08.549
THESE ARE AMAZING.
- MM-HMM.

04:08.582 --> 04:10.484
- THANK YOU, GOOD SIR.

04:10.518 --> 04:12.886
- AND NOW YOU'RE MAKING HIM
FEEL VERY UNCOMFORTABLE.

04:12.920 --> 04:14.254
- OH, NO, NO, NO.
THE FACT THAT

04:14.288 --> 04:15.723
A DEAD RINGER, JOHNNY--
AND I DO MEAN DEAD--

04:15.756 --> 04:17.090
FOR YOUR FATHER PASSED AWAY
IN THE RIG,

04:17.124 --> 04:18.826
AND YOU SEEM COMPLETELY
UNAFFECTED BY IT.

04:18.859 --> 04:20.394
- WHAT ARE YOU
TALKING ABOUT?

04:20.428 --> 04:21.929
- BIG STRONG IRISH GUY.

04:21.962 --> 04:25.966
65 YEARS OLD.

04:25.999 --> 04:28.469
- WAIT.
- WHITE HAIR, BLUE EYES.

04:28.502 --> 04:30.604
- OH, MY GOD.

04:30.638 --> 04:33.240
- EVEN HAD THE SAME COLOGNE--
OLD SPICE.

04:33.273 --> 04:36.209
- IT'S A MASCULINE SCENT.

04:37.778 --> 04:39.847
- HOLY SH--.
THAT'S AWESOME.

04:39.880 --> 04:41.449
- WHY IS IT AWESOME?

04:41.482 --> 04:43.684
- UM, MY DAD LEFT MY MOM

04:43.717 --> 04:46.420
FOR A STRIPPER NAMED COCO
WHEN I WAS 13.

04:46.454 --> 04:47.855
THE FACT THAT
HIS DOPPELGANGER

04:47.888 --> 04:49.323
BIT THE DUST
RIGHT IN FRONT OF ME

04:49.357 --> 04:51.024
AND I DIDN'T EVEN FLINCH,
THAT MEANS

04:51.058 --> 04:52.460
IT'S LIKE HE'S COMPLETELY
OUT OF MY SYSTEM.

04:52.493 --> 04:54.495
THE GUY LOOKED AND SMELLED

04:54.528 --> 04:56.296
AND EVEN DRESSED
JUST LIKE MY OLD MAN,

04:56.330 --> 04:57.831
AND I DIDN'T EVEN NOTICE.

04:57.865 --> 04:59.333
IT'S LIKE THE GUY
DOESN'T EXIST ANYMORE.

04:59.367 --> 05:00.701
[giggles]
GO HIGH, BRO.

05:00.734 --> 05:01.769
- WHEN'S THE LAST TIME
YOU TALKED

05:01.802 --> 05:02.836
TO YOUR FATHER, JOHN?

05:02.870 --> 05:04.137
- UH, I DON'T REMEMBER.

05:04.171 --> 05:06.306
- SEVEN YEARS, JOHN.
I KEPT TRACK.

05:06.340 --> 05:07.941
- SEVEN YEARS.
- MM-HMM.

05:07.975 --> 05:09.610
- WOW. GIVE ME SOME, BRIAN.

05:09.643 --> 05:11.812
- THIS IS RIDICULOUS, JOHNNY.
- WHAT?

05:11.845 --> 05:13.947
- IF THAT HAD BEEN YOUR DAD
WHO DROPPED DEAD TODAY,

05:13.981 --> 05:15.649
YOU WOULD HAVE MILES
AND MILES

05:15.683 --> 05:17.485
OF UNRESOLVED ISSUES WITH IT.
- N--

05:17.518 --> 05:19.019
- AND THEY WOULD HAUNT YOU--
AND ME,

05:19.052 --> 05:20.721
AS THE GUY WHO'S GOT TO LISTEN
TO YOU BITCH--

05:20.754 --> 05:22.055
FOR THE REST OF YOUR LIFE.
- I DON'T THINK SO.

05:22.089 --> 05:23.691
- THIS IS SAD.
THIS IS REALLY SAD.

05:23.724 --> 05:26.193
IT'S LIKE A DEPRESSING
GUS VAN SANT MOVIE

05:26.226 --> 05:29.630
WHEN IT COULD BE
A ROB LOWE HALLMARK SPECIAL.

05:29.663 --> 05:32.299
- ROB LOWE?

05:32.332 --> 05:38.005
- YOU GUYS NEVER SAW
THE CHRISTMAS SHOES?

05:38.038 --> 05:40.641
OH, MY GOD.
IT'S SO GOOD.

05:40.674 --> 05:43.844
